<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<mx:Application xmlns:mx="http://www.adobe.com/2006/mxml">

  <mx:HTTPService id="srv" url="data.xml"/>

  <mx:Label text="# items = {srv.lastResult.item.length}" creationComplete="srv.send()"/>


  <!--
       Given the following data.xml file:
       <item label="Item 1"/>
       <item label="Item 2"/>

       And given the following Flex code:
       <mx:HTTPService id="srv" url="data.xml"/>

       <mx:Label text="# items = {srv.lastResult.item.length}" creationComplete="srv.send()"/>

       The Label displays "# items = 2".  What does the Label display when only one item is in the XML data?

       A) # items = undefined

       B) # items = 1

       C) There is a runtime error.

       D) The code does not compile.


       Answer: A
       Reason: By default XML is only converted to Arrays when there is more than one repeated node.  Otherwise the item is just an Object.

       Author: James Ward (www.jamesward.com)
  -->

</mx:Application>